column1: We obtained similar results for Sv2c, a synaptic vesicle protein found in SACs [ 40]; Kcnc1b and Kcnc2, potassium channels expressed on SAC soma and dendrites as well as a very small number of ganglion cells [ 41]; gamma - aminobutyric acid ( GABA), an inhibitory neurotransmitter present in about half of amacrine cells including SACs, as well as horizontal and some bipolar neurons [ 37]; and Calb1 ( calbindin), which is expressed in many amacrine cells and labels SAC process faintly ( Figure S7A and S7B; Table S1; and data not shown).
